{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Everybody talks about happiness these days."},{"time":3000,"text":"I had somebody count the number of books"},{"time":6000,"text":"with \"happiness\" in the title published in the last five years"},{"time":9000,"text":"and they gave up after about 40, and there were many more."},{"time":14000,"text":"There is a huge wave of interest in happiness,"},{"time":17000,"text":"among researchers."},{"time":19000,"text":"There is a lot of happiness coaching."},{"time":21000,"text":"Everybody would like to make people happier."},{"time":23000,"text":"But in spite of all this flood of work,"},{"time":27000,"text":"there are several cognitive traps"},{"time":29000,"text":"that sort of make it almost impossible to think straight"},{"time":32000,"text":"about happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"And my talk today will be mostly about these cognitive traps."},{"time":37000,"text":"This applies to laypeople thinking about their own happiness,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and it applies to scholars thinking about happiness,"},{"time":43000,"text":"because it turns out we're just as messed up as anybody else is."},{"time":47000,"text":"The first of these traps"},{"time":49000,"text":"is a reluctance to admit complexity."},{"time":52000,"text":"It turns out that the word \"happiness\""},{"time":55000,"text":"is just not a useful word anymore,"},{"time":58000,"text":"because we apply it to too many different things."},{"time":61000,"text":"I think there is one particular meaning to which we might restrict it,"},{"time":64000,"text":"but by and large,"},{"time":66000,"text":"this is something that we'll have to give up"},{"time":68000,"text":"and we'll have to adopt the more complicated view"},{"time":72000,"text":"of what well-being is."},{"time":74000,"text":"The second trap is a confusion between experience and memory;"},{"time":78000,"text":"basically, it's between being happy in your life,"},{"time":81000,"text":"and being happy about your life"},{"time":83000,"text":"or happy with your life."},{"time":85000,"text":"And those are two very different concepts,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and they're both lumped in the notion of happiness."},{"time":90000,"text":"And the third is the focusing illusion,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and it's the unfortunate fact that we can't think about any circumstance"},{"time":96000,"text":"that affects well-being"},{"time":98000,"text":"without distorting its importance."},{"time":100000,"text":"I mean, this is a real cognitive trap."},{"time":103000,"text":"There's just no way of getting it right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"Now, I'd like to start with an example"},{"time":108000,"text":"of somebody who had a question-and-answer session"},{"time":113000,"text":"after one of my lectures reported a story,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and that was a story --"},{"time":118000,"text":"He said he'd been listening to a symphony,"},{"time":121000,"text":"and it was absolutely glorious music"},{"time":124000,"text":"and at the very end of the recording,"},{"time":127000,"text":"there was a dreadful screeching sound."},{"time":129000,"text":"And then he added, really quite emotionally,"},{"time":131000,"text":"it ruined the whole experience."},{"time":135000,"text":"But it hadn't."},{"time":137000,"text":"What it had ruined were the memories of the experience."},{"time":140000,"text":"He had had the experience."},{"time":142000,"text":"He had had 20 minutes of glorious music."},{"time":144000,"text":"They counted for nothing"},{"time":146000,"text":"because he was left with a memory;"},{"time":149000,"text":"the memory was ruined,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and the memory was all that he had gotten to keep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154000,"text":"What this is telling us, really,"},{"time":157000,"text":"is that we might be thinking of ourselves and of other people"},{"time":159000,"text":"in terms of two selves."},{"time":161000,"text":"There is an experiencing self,"},{"time":164000,"text":"who lives in the present"},{"time":166000,"text":"and knows the present,"},{"time":168000,"text":"is capable of re-living the past,"},{"time":170000,"text":"but basically it has only the present."},{"time":173000,"text":"It's the experiencing self that the doctor approaches --"},{"time":176000,"text":"you know, when the doctor asks,"},{"time":177000,"text":"\"Does it hurt now when I touch you here?\""},{"time":181000,"text":"And then there is a remembering self,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and the remembering self is the one that keeps score,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and maintains the story of our life,"},{"time":190000,"text":"and it's the one that the doctor approaches"},{"time":193000,"text":"in asking the question,"},{"time":195000,"text":"\"How have you been feeling lately?\""},{"time":198000,"text":"or \"How was your trip to Albania?\" or something like that."},{"time":201000,"text":"Those are two very different entities,"},{"time":204000,"text":"the experiencing self and the remembering self,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and getting confused between them is part of the mess"},{"time":211000,"text":"about the notion of happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214000,"text":"Now, the remembering self"},{"time":217000,"text":"is a storyteller."},{"time":220000,"text":"And that really starts with a basic response of our memories --"},{"time":224000,"text":"it starts immediately."},{"time":226000,"text":"We don't only tell stories when we set out to tell stories."},{"time":229000,"text":"Our memory tells us stories,"},{"time":232000,"text":"that is, what we get to keep from our experiences"},{"time":234000,"text":"is a story."},{"time":236000,"text":"And let me begin with one example."},{"time":241000,"text":"This is an old study."},{"time":243000,"text":"Those are actual patients undergoing a painful procedure."},{"time":246000,"text":"I won't go into detail. It's no longer painful these days,"},{"time":249000,"text":"but it was painful when this study was run in the 1990s."},{"time":253000,"text":"They were asked to report on their pain every 60 seconds."},{"time":256000,"text":"Here are two patients,"},{"time":259000,"text":"those are their recordings."},{"time":261000,"text":"And you are asked, \"Who of them suffered more?\""},{"time":264000,"text":"And it's a very easy question."},{"time":266000,"text":"Clearly, Patient B suffered more --"},{"time":268000,"text":"his colonoscopy was longer,"},{"time":270000,"text":"and every minute of pain that Patient A had,"},{"time":273000,"text":"Patient B had, and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"But now there is another question:"},{"time":279000,"text":"\"How much did these patients think they suffered?\""},{"time":282000,"text":"And here is a surprise."},{"time":284000,"text":"The surprise is that Patient A"},{"time":286000,"text":"had a much worse memory of the colonoscopy"},{"time":289000,"text":"than Patient B."},{"time":291000,"text":"The stories of the colonoscopies were different,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and because a very critical part of the story is how it ends."},{"time":300000,"text":"And neither of these stories is very inspiring or great --"},{"time":303000,"text":"but one of them is this distinct ... (Laughter)"},{"time":307000,"text":"but one of them is distinctly worse than the other."},{"time":310000,"text":"And the one that is worse"},{"time":312000,"text":"is the one where pain was at its peak at the very end;"},{"time":315000,"text":"it's a bad story."},{"time":317000,"text":"How do we know that?"},{"time":319000,"text":"Because we asked these people after their colonoscopy,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and much later, too,"},{"time":323000,"text":"\"How bad was the whole thing, in total?\""},{"time":325000,"text":"And it was much worse for A than for B, in memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Now this is a direct conflict"},{"time":331000,"text":"between the experiencing self and the remembering self."},{"time":334000,"text":"From the point of view of the experiencing self,"},{"time":337000,"text":"clearly, B had a worse time."},{"time":339000,"text":"Now, what you could do with Patient A,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and we actually ran clinical experiments,"},{"time":345000,"text":"and it has been done, and it does work --"},{"time":347000,"text":"you could actually extend the colonoscopy of Patient A"},{"time":352000,"text":"by just keeping the tube in without jiggling it too much."},{"time":355000,"text":"That will cause the patient"},{"time":358000,"text":"to suffer, but just a little"},{"time":361000,"text":"and much less than before."},{"time":363000,"text":"And if you do that for a couple of minutes,"},{"time":365000,"text":"you have made the experiencing self"},{"time":367000,"text":"of Patient A worse off,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and you have the remembering self of Patient A"},{"time":372000,"text":"a lot better off,"},{"time":374000,"text":"because now you have endowed Patient A"},{"time":376000,"text":"with a better story"},{"time":378000,"text":"about his experience."},{"time":381000,"text":"What defines a story?"},{"time":384000,"text":"And that is true of the stories"},{"time":386000,"text":"that memory delivers for us,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and it's also true of the stories that we make up."},{"time":391000,"text":"What defines a story are changes,"},{"time":395000,"text":"significant moments and endings."},{"time":398000,"text":"Endings are very, very important"},{"time":400000,"text":"and, in this case, the ending dominated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"Now, the experiencing self"},{"time":406000,"text":"lives its life continuously."},{"time":409000,"text":"It has moments of experience, one after the other."},{"time":412000,"text":"And you can ask: What happens to these moments?"},{"time":415000,"text":"And the answer is really straightforward:"},{"time":417000,"text":"They are lost forever."},{"time":419000,"text":"I mean, most of the moments of our life --"},{"time":421000,"text":"and I calculated, you know, the psychological present"},{"time":424000,"text":"is said to be about three seconds long;"},{"time":426000,"text":"that means that, you know,"},{"time":428000,"text":"in a life there are about 600 million of them;"},{"time":430000,"text":"in a month, there are about 600,000 --"},{"time":433000,"text":"most of them don't leave a trace."},{"time":437000,"text":"Most of them are completely ignored"},{"time":439000,"text":"by the remembering self."},{"time":441000,"text":"And yet, somehow you get the sense"},{"time":443000,"text":"that they should count,"},{"time":445000,"text":"that what happens during these moments of experience"},{"time":448000,"text":"is our life."},{"time":450000,"text":"It's the finite resource that we're spending"},{"time":452000,"text":"while we're on this earth."},{"time":454000,"text":"And how to spend it"},{"time":456000,"text":"would seem to be relevant,"},{"time":458000,"text":"but that is not the story"},{"time":460000,"text":"that the remembering self keeps for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"So we have the remembering self"},{"time":464000,"text":"and the experiencing self,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and they're really quite distinct."},{"time":468000,"text":"The biggest difference between them"},{"time":470000,"text":"is in the handling of time."},{"time":473000,"text":"From the point of view of the experiencing self,"},{"time":476000,"text":"if you have a vacation,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and the second week is just as good as the first,"},{"time":481000,"text":"then the two-week vacation"},{"time":484000,"text":"is twice as good as the one-week vacation."},{"time":487000,"text":"That's not the way it works at all for the remembering self."},{"time":490000,"text":"For the remembering self, a two-week vacation"},{"time":492000,"text":"is barely better than the one-week vacation"},{"time":495000,"text":"because there are no new memories added."},{"time":497000,"text":"You have not changed the story."},{"time":500000,"text":"And in this way,"},{"time":502000,"text":"time is actually the critical variable"},{"time":505000,"text":"that distinguishes a remembering self"},{"time":508000,"text":"from an experiencing self;"},{"time":510000,"text":"time has very little impact on the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514000,"text":"Now, the remembering self does more"},{"time":517000,"text":"than remember and tell stories."},{"time":519000,"text":"It is actually the one that makes decisions"},{"time":523000,"text":"because, if you have a patient who has had, say,"},{"time":525000,"text":"two colonoscopies with two different surgeons"},{"time":528000,"text":"and is deciding which of them to choose,"},{"time":531000,"text":"then the one that chooses"},{"time":534000,"text":"is the one that has the memory that is less bad,"},{"time":538000,"text":"and that's the surgeon that will be chosen."},{"time":540000,"text":"The experiencing self"},{"time":542000,"text":"has no voice in this choice."},{"time":545000,"text":"We actually don't choose between experiences,"},{"time":548000,"text":"we choose between memories of experiences."},{"time":551000,"text":"And even when we think about the future,"},{"time":554000,"text":"we don't think of our future normally as experiences."},{"time":557000,"text":"We think of our future"},{"time":559000,"text":"as anticipated memories."},{"time":562000,"text":"And basically you can look at this,"},{"time":564000,"text":"you know, as a tyranny of the remembering self,"},{"time":567000,"text":"and you can think of the remembering self"},{"time":569000,"text":"sort of dragging the experiencing self"},{"time":571000,"text":"through experiences that"},{"time":573000,"text":"the experiencing self doesn't need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"I have that sense that"},{"time":577000,"text":"when we go on vacations"},{"time":579000,"text":"this is very frequently the case;"},{"time":581000,"text":"that is, we go on vacations,"},{"time":583000,"text":"to a very large extent,"},{"time":585000,"text":"in the service of our remembering self."},{"time":588000,"text":"And this is a bit hard to justify I think."},{"time":591000,"text":"I mean, how much do we consume our memories?"},{"time":594000,"text":"That is one of the explanations"},{"time":596000,"text":"that is given for the dominance"},{"time":598000,"text":"of the remembering self."},{"time":600000,"text":"And when I think about that, I think about a vacation"},{"time":602000,"text":"we had in Antarctica a few years ago,"},{"time":605000,"text":"which was clearly the best vacation I've ever had,"},{"time":608000,"text":"and I think of it relatively often,"},{"time":610000,"text":"relative to how much I think of other vacations."},{"time":612000,"text":"And I probably have consumed"},{"time":616000,"text":"my memories of that three-week trip, I would say,"},{"time":618000,"text":"for about 25 minutes in the last four years."},{"time":621000,"text":"Now, if I had ever opened the folder"},{"time":624000,"text":"with the 600 pictures in it,"},{"time":627000,"text":"I would have spent another hour."},{"time":629000,"text":"Now, that is three weeks,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and that is at most an hour and a half."},{"time":633000,"text":"There seems to be a discrepancy."},{"time":635000,"text":"Now, I may be a bit extreme, you know,"},{"time":637000,"text":"in how little appetite I have for consuming memories,"},{"time":640000,"text":"but even if you do more of this,"},{"time":643000,"text":"there is a genuine question:"},{"time":646000,"text":"Why do we put so much weight on memory"},{"time":650000,"text":"relative to the weight that we put on experiences?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"So I want you to think"},{"time":655000,"text":"about a thought experiment."},{"time":658000,"text":"Imagine that for your next vacation,"},{"time":660000,"text":"you know that at the end of the vacation"},{"time":663000,"text":"all your pictures will be destroyed,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and you'll get an amnesic drug"},{"time":668000,"text":"so that you won't remember anything."},{"time":670000,"text":"Now, would you choose the same vacation? (Laughter)"},{"time":674000,"text":"And if you would choose a different vacation,"},{"time":679000,"text":"there is a conflict between your two selves,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and you need to think about how to adjudicate that conflict,"},{"time":684000,"text":"and it's actually not at all obvious, because"},{"time":687000,"text":"if you think in terms of time,"},{"time":690000,"text":"then you get one answer,"},{"time":693000,"text":"and if you think in terms of memories,"},{"time":696000,"text":"you might get another answer."},{"time":698000,"text":"Why do we pick the vacations we do"},{"time":701000,"text":"is a problem that confronts us"},{"time":704000,"text":"with a choice between the two selves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706000,"text":"Now, the two selves"},{"time":709000,"text":"bring up two notions of happiness."},{"time":711000,"text":"There are really two concepts of happiness"},{"time":713000,"text":"that we can apply, one per self."},{"time":716000,"text":"So you can ask: How happy is the experiencing self?"},{"time":721000,"text":"And then you would ask: How happy are the moments"},{"time":723000,"text":"in the experiencing self's life?"},{"time":726000,"text":"And they're all -- happiness for moments"},{"time":728000,"text":"is a fairly complicated process."},{"time":730000,"text":"What are the emotions that can be measured?"},{"time":733000,"text":"And, by the way, now we are capable"},{"time":735000,"text":"of getting a pretty good idea"},{"time":737000,"text":"of the happiness of the experiencing self over time."},{"time":743000,"text":"If you ask for the happiness of the remembering self,"},{"time":746000,"text":"it's a completely different thing."},{"time":748000,"text":"This is not about how happily a person lives."},{"time":751000,"text":"It is about how satisfied or pleased the person is"},{"time":754000,"text":"when that person thinks about her life."},{"time":758000,"text":"Very different notion."},{"time":760000,"text":"Anyone who doesn't distinguish those notions"},{"time":763000,"text":"is going to mess up the study of happiness,"},{"time":765000,"text":"and I belong to a crowd of students of well-being,"},{"time":768000,"text":"who've been messing up the study of happiness for a long time"},{"time":772000,"text":"in precisely this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"The distinction between the"},{"time":776000,"text":"happiness of the experiencing self"},{"time":778000,"text":"and the satisfaction of the remembering self"},{"time":781000,"text":"has been recognized in recent years,"},{"time":783000,"text":"and there are now efforts to measure the two separately."},{"time":786000,"text":"The Gallup Organization has a world poll"},{"time":789000,"text":"where more than half a million people"},{"time":791000,"text":"have been asked questions"},{"time":793000,"text":"about what they think of their life"},{"time":795000,"text":"and about their experiences,"},{"time":797000,"text":"and there have been other efforts along those lines."},{"time":800000,"text":"So in recent years, we have begun to learn"},{"time":803000,"text":"about the happiness of the two selves."},{"time":806000,"text":"And the main lesson I think that we have learned"},{"time":809000,"text":"is they are really different."},{"time":811000,"text":"You can know how satisfied somebody is with their life,"},{"time":816000,"text":"and that really doesn't teach you much"},{"time":818000,"text":"about how happily they're living their life,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and vice versa."},{"time":823000,"text":"Just to give you a sense of the correlation,"},{"time":825000,"text":"the correlation is about .5."},{"time":827000,"text":"What that means is if you met somebody,"},{"time":830000,"text":"and you were told, \"Oh his father is six feet tall,\""},{"time":834000,"text":"how much would you know about his height?"},{"time":836000,"text":"Well, you would know something about his height,"},{"time":838000,"text":"but there's a lot of uncertainty."},{"time":840000,"text":"You have that much uncertainty."},{"time":842000,"text":"If I tell you that somebody ranked their life eight on a scale of ten,"},{"time":846000,"text":"you have a lot of uncertainty"},{"time":848000,"text":"about how happy they are"},{"time":850000,"text":"with their experiencing self."},{"time":852000,"text":"So the correlation is low."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"We know something about what controls"},{"time":857000,"text":"satisfaction of the happiness self."},{"time":859000,"text":"We know that money is very important,"},{"time":861000,"text":"goals are very important."},{"time":863000,"text":"We know that happiness is mainly"},{"time":867000,"text":"being satisfied with people that we like,"},{"time":870000,"text":"spending time with people that we like."},{"time":873000,"text":"There are other pleasures, but this is dominant."},{"time":875000,"text":"So if you want to maximize the happiness of the two selves,"},{"time":878000,"text":"you are going to end up"},{"time":880000,"text":"doing very different things."},{"time":882000,"text":"The bottom line of what I've said here"},{"time":884000,"text":"is that we really should not think of happiness"},{"time":888000,"text":"as a substitute for well-being."},{"time":890000,"text":"It is a completely different notion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893000,"text":"Now, very quickly,"},{"time":896000,"text":"another reason we cannot think straight about happiness"},{"time":900000,"text":"is that we do not attend to the same things"},{"time":907000,"text":"when we think about life, and we actually live."},{"time":910000,"text":"So, if you ask the simple question of how happy people are in California,"},{"time":915000,"text":"you are not going to get to the correct answer."},{"time":918000,"text":"When you ask that question,"},{"time":920000,"text":"you think people must be happier in California"},{"time":922000,"text":"if, say, you live in Ohio."},{"time":924000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":926000,"text":"And what happens is"},{"time":929000,"text":"when you think about living in California,"},{"time":933000,"text":"you are thinking of the contrast"},{"time":935000,"text":"between California and other places,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and that contrast, say, is in climate."},{"time":940000,"text":"Well, it turns out that climate"},{"time":942000,"text":"is not very important to the experiencing self"},{"time":945000,"text":"and it's not even very important to the reflective self"},{"time":948000,"text":"that decides how happy people are."},{"time":951000,"text":"But now, because the reflective self is in charge,"},{"time":955000,"text":"you may end up -- some people may end up"},{"time":957000,"text":"moving to California."},{"time":959000,"text":"And it's sort of interesting to trace what is going to happen"},{"time":962000,"text":"to people who move to California in the hope of getting happier."},{"time":965000,"text":"Well, their experiencing self"},{"time":967000,"text":"is not going to get happier."},{"time":969000,"text":"We know that."},{"time":972000,"text":"But one thing will happen: They will think they are happier,"},{"time":975000,"text":"because, when they think about it,"},{"time":979000,"text":"they'll be reminded of how horrible the weather was in Ohio,"},{"time":983000,"text":"and they will feel they made the right decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"It is very difficult"},{"time":988000,"text":"to think straight about well-being,"},{"time":990000,"text":"and I hope I have given you a sense"},{"time":993000,"text":"of how difficult it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":997000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you. I've got a question for you."},{"time":1004000,"text":"Thank you so much."},{"time":1006000,"text":"Now, when we were on the phone a few weeks ago,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"you mentioned to me that there was quite an interesting result"},{"time":1013000,"text":"came out of that Gallup survey."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Is that something you can share"},{"time":1017000,"text":"since you do have a few moments left now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019000,"text":"Daniel Kahneman: Sure."},{"time":1021000,"text":"I think the most interesting result that we found in the Gallup survey"},{"time":1024000,"text":"is a number, which we absolutely did not expect to find."},{"time":1027000,"text":"We found that with respect to the happiness"},{"time":1029000,"text":"of the experiencing self."},{"time":1032000,"text":"When we looked at how feelings,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"vary with income."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And it turns out that, below an income"},{"time":1042000,"text":"of 60,000 dollars a year, for Americans --"},{"time":1045000,"text":"and that's a very large sample of Americans, like 600,000,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"so it's a large representative sample --"},{"time":1050000,"text":"below an income of 600,000 dollars a year..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1052000,"text":"CA: 60,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"DK: 60,000."},{"time":1056000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1058000,"text":"60,000 dollars a year, people are unhappy,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"and they get progressively unhappier the poorer they get."},{"time":1065000,"text":"Above that, we get an absolutely flat line."},{"time":1068000,"text":"I mean I've rarely seen lines so flat."},{"time":1071000,"text":"Clearly, what is happening is"},{"time":1073000,"text":"money does not buy you experiential happiness,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"but lack of money certainly buys you misery,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and we can measure that misery"},{"time":1081000,"text":"very, very clearly."},{"time":1083000,"text":"In terms of the other self, the remembering self,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"you get a different story."},{"time":1088000,"text":"The more money you earn, the more satisfied you are."},{"time":1091000,"text":"That does not hold for emotions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1093000,"text":"CA: But Danny, the whole American endeavor is about"},{"time":1096000,"text":"life, liberty, the pursuit of happiness."},{"time":1099000,"text":"If people took seriously that finding,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"I mean, it seems to turn upside down"},{"time":1106000,"text":"everything we believe about, like for example,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"taxation policy and so forth."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Is there any chance that politicians, that the country generally,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"would take a finding like that seriously"},{"time":1116000,"text":"and run public policy based on it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118000,"text":"DK: You know I think that there is recognition"},{"time":1120000,"text":"of the role of happiness research in public policy."},{"time":1123000,"text":"The recognition is going to be slow in the United States,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"no question about that,"},{"time":1127000,"text":"but in the U.K., it is happening,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"and in other countries it is happening."},{"time":1131000,"text":"People are recognizing that they ought"},{"time":1134000,"text":"to be thinking of happiness"},{"time":1136000,"text":"when they think of public policy."},{"time":1138000,"text":"It's going to take a while,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"and people are going to debate"},{"time":1143000,"text":"whether they want to study experience happiness,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"or whether they want to study life evaluation,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"so we need to have that debate fairly soon."},{"time":1150000,"text":"How to enhance happiness"},{"time":1152000,"text":"goes very different ways depending on how you think,"},{"time":1155000,"text":"and whether you think of the remembering self"},{"time":1157000,"text":"or you think of the experiencing self."},{"time":1159000,"text":"This is going to influence policy, I think, in years to come."},{"time":1162000,"text":"In the United States, efforts are being made"},{"time":1165000,"text":"to measure the experience happiness of the population."},{"time":1168000,"text":"This is going to be, I think, within the next decade or two,"},{"time":1171000,"text":"part of national statistics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1173000,"text":"CA: Well, it seems to me that this issue will -- or at least should be --"},{"time":1177000,"text":"the most interesting policy discussion to track"},{"time":1179000,"text":"over the next few years."},{"time":1181000,"text":"Thank you so much for inventing behavioral economics."},{"time":1183000,"text":"Thank you, Danny Kahneman."}]}]}